To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Tennessee Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

The term “document(s)” used herein includes, but is not limited to, electronic mail, notes and any related maps.

• All procurement document(s) related to the installation and use of vehicle-mounted/mobile automated license plate reader (ALPR) system;
• Document(s) relating to mobile ALPR camera numbers in use and or planned;
• Document(s) of the name(s) and number(s) of mobile ALPR camera make(s) and model(s) in use;
• Document(s) pertaining to “hot list(s)” or “watch list(s)” created and in use with the mobile ALPR system(s);
• Documentation pertaining to ALPR system data retention policy;
• Documentation regarding the number of license plates scanned with any mobile ALPR system for the last 30 days;
• Documentation pertaining to the number of “hits” on “hot” or “watch list(s)” in the mobile ALPR system for the last 30 days;
• Documentation relating to the number of times ALPR system data was accessed/searched and for what reason for the last 30 days;
• Copy of ALPR system audit log(s)/record(s) for the last 30 days;
• Copy of policy regarding use of ALPRs and access misuse of any ALPR system;
• Disciplinary record(s) for any user abusing access to and use of ALPR system data;
• Memorandum(s), note(s), electronic-mail regarding public notification of implementation of ALPR system;
• Any formal public release notice(s) regarding implementation of ALPR system.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 7 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Kent Hoover, a citizen of Tennessee, in coordination with Elizabethton Surveillance.
